003, 2006.","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Isabel ."],"variants":[{"name":"Isabel","meanings":["Originally a Spanish version of   Elizabeth  , which was coined by deletion of the first syllable and alteration of the final consonant sound to one that can normally end a word in Spanish. The name was imported into France in the early Middle Ages, and thence into England. It was a royal name, and its enduring popularity may have been enhanced by the fact that it was borne by a queen of England—  Isabella  (  1296–1358 ), daughter of  Philip IV  of France—even though she led a turbulent life and eventually had her husband,  Edward II , murdered."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Isobel Sandon was born in 1400, in Leicester, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom, her father, William Sandon, was 20 and her mother, Christiana, was 16. She had at least 1 son with John Belgrave."},"et":{"1400–":"1400–Surnud","1400–1420":"1400–1420","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1397–Male":"1397–Surnud","1419–1468":"1419–1468","1380–1400":"1380–1400","1385–1400":"1385–1400","1468":"1468","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1397":"1397","1385":"1385","1419":"1419","1380":"1380","Belgrave, Leicester, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicester, Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, England"},"fi":{"1400–":"1400–Kuollut","1400–1420":"1400–1420","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1397–Male":"1397–Kuollut","1419–1468":"1419–1468","1380–1400":"1380–1400","1385–1400":"1385–1400","1468":"1468","1400":"1400","1420":"1420","1397":"1397","1385":"1385","1419":"1419","1380":"1380","Belgrave, Leicester, Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Leicester, Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Belgrave, Leicestershire, England":"Belgrave, Leicestershire, England"},"fr":{"1400–":"1400–Décédée","1400–1420":"1400–1420","1400–Female":"1400–Décédée","1397–Male":"1397–Décédé","1419–1468":"1419–1468","1380–1400":"1380–1400","1385–1400":"138